WEBVTT

00:02.117 --> 00:04.051
Why don't you guys stay here in L.A.?

00:04.086 --> 00:06.464
Then, that way, me and Scotty can
see each other whenever we want.

00:06.489 --> 00:08.523
I could get into some socal living.

00:08.548 --> 00:10.094
<i>Previously on Mistresses... </i>

00:10.125 --> 00:13.029
Patient's my wife. We are having
trouble finding a blood match for her.

00:13.054 --> 00:14.164
She's dying.

00:14.164 --> 00:17.600
- Why would you do this for me?
- I want to believe in something.

00:17.639 --> 00:19.769
Was she everything you thought she'd be?

00:20.827 --> 00:23.494
This really can't be how our story begins.

00:23.518 --> 00:25.647
I love you. And I know
that I will be with you,

00:25.685 --> 00:26.941
but not right now.

00:26.971 --> 00:30.369
<i>The number you've reached has been
disconnected or is no longer in service.</i>

00:32.974 --> 00:35.877
[Shower running]

00:35.960 --> 00:38.817
♪ Say you love me ♪

00:40.564 --> 00:42.380
♪ to my face ♪

00:44.301 --> 00:47.222
♪ I need it more ♪

00:48.372 --> 00:50.806
♪ than your embrace ♪

00:52.076 --> 00:55.138
♪ just say you want me ♪

00:56.280 --> 00:58.977
♪ that's all it takes ♪

01:00.184 --> 01:03.313
♪ heart's getting torn ♪

01:04.655 --> 01:07.403
♪ from your mistakes ♪

01:08.692 --> 01:11.990
♪ 'cause I don't want to fall in love ♪

01:12.830 --> 01:15.325
♪ if you don't want to try ♪

01:17.118 --> 01:20.569
♪ but all that I've been thinking of ♪

01:20.611 --> 01:23.612
- ♪ is maybe that you might ♪
- Come on, come on.

01:23.774 --> 01:25.759
Just give me a freakin' space already.

01:25.784 --> 01:28.084
[Cellphone rings] [Sighs]

01:28.119 --> 01:29.752
- [Cellphone beeps]
- Hello?

01:29.788 --> 01:31.754
Joss, where have you been?

01:31.790 --> 01:33.356
Oh, you know, driving around

01:33.391 --> 01:36.125
for 95 hours because
parking sucks in this city.

01:36.161 --> 01:38.337
No, I mean I never see you.

01:38.362 --> 01:40.240
The only reason I know
you're living with me

01:40.265 --> 01:42.366
is there's a pop-tart under the couch.

01:42.391 --> 01:44.191
Yeah, well, I've been, you know,

01:44.216 --> 01:46.216
spending a lot of time at that
coffee shop around the corner.

01:46.241 --> 01:47.341
Doing what?

01:47.366 --> 01:48.885
Something you won't approve of.

01:48.910 --> 01:50.209
Caffeine after 2:00?

01:50.234 --> 01:52.718
- Drafting an apology e-mail to Savi.
- Joss.

01:52.743 --> 01:54.841
If you'd have helped
me with the last one...

01:54.866 --> 01:57.633
The last one was insane... It was 27 pages.

01:57.658 --> 01:59.125
Really, Karen? Is that a fact?

01:59.150 --> 02:00.549
Because e-mails don't paginate.

02:00.584 --> 02:01.984
Honey, listen to me,

02:02.019 --> 02:03.685
you've got to let this go.

02:03.721 --> 02:05.187
She's not writing you back.

02:05.222 --> 02:06.455
She's not writing me back,

02:06.490 --> 02:07.856
and I didn't screw her ex-husband.

02:07.892 --> 02:08.924
I didn't screw him.

02:08.959 --> 02:10.526
Sorry... grind him

02:10.561 --> 02:12.227
in your wedding dress
while she held your bouquet.

02:12.263 --> 02:14.775
See? I knew you were mad.

02:15.006 --> 02:16.373
No, I'm not mad.

02:16.398 --> 02:18.059
I'm trying to help you.

02:18.084 --> 02:19.416
Your time would be better spent

02:19.441 --> 02:21.078
repairing your jobless/homeless situation.

02:21.103 --> 02:22.469
You're jobless, too.

02:22.504 --> 02:24.351
I did a shift at the hospital yesterday,

02:24.376 --> 02:26.610
and my unicorn blood
goes into Vivian tomorrow.

02:26.635 --> 02:28.358
So, you're employed and a saint.

02:28.377 --> 02:30.543
Th-th-that's, uh, wonderful.
I feel so much better.

02:30.579 --> 02:33.177
- Thank you for calling.
- Honey, come on.

02:33.202 --> 02:35.869
- I didn't mean...
- No, it's fine. You're right.

02:35.894 --> 02:37.326
I... I know. I... I just...

02:37.351 --> 02:39.157
I-I shouldn't fixate on Savi.

02:40.443 --> 02:42.243
Oh, I see a spot. I got to go.

02:42.278 --> 02:43.677
Jo...

02:49.185 --> 02:50.618
[Tires squeal]

02:52.955 --> 02:55.065
Oh, my God. Are you kidding me?

02:55.090 --> 02:56.765
No frickin' way.

02:58.553 --> 03:01.093
Uh, excuse me. Hello?

03:01.297 --> 03:02.692
Excuse me.

03:03.766 --> 03:05.032
Yes?

03:05.067 --> 03:06.433
- "Y-yes"?
- Mm.

03:06.469 --> 03:08.836
Are you seriously playing dumb
right now? You know what you did.

03:08.871 --> 03:11.037
Oh, just... here. Here.

03:11.062 --> 03:12.691
Here, here, here. Take this.

03:12.716 --> 03:14.199
What the hell is this?

03:14.224 --> 03:15.524
It's American paper money.

03:15.549 --> 03:17.082
You probably used one or two of these

03:17.107 --> 03:19.106
to buy your sweet little car back there.

03:19.131 --> 03:20.964
Okay, I'll have you know
that that's a rental.

03:20.989 --> 03:22.355
Wonderful.

03:22.807 --> 03:24.206
Wow.

03:24.670 --> 03:26.236
You know what? You're not fooling anyone

03:26.261 --> 03:28.467
with your spray tan and
your range rover, by the way.

03:28.492 --> 03:30.875
You may look happy, but you're
not... You're dead inside.

03:30.940 --> 03:32.740
Dead inside!

03:35.336 --> 03:37.188
Mistresses 3x02
I'll Be Watching You

03:37.626 --> 03:40.842
Sync and corrections by Albanda
www.Addic7ed.com

03:41.923 --> 03:44.233
April: Lucy, hurry up! We're
gonna be late for church.

03:44.258 --> 03:46.458
I'm not sitting next to you in God's house.

03:46.483 --> 03:49.493
[Door slams, doorbell rings]

03:53.772 --> 03:55.133
- Yes?
- Hey,

03:55.158 --> 03:57.757
I'm sorry to pop in, but I got
kind of a quarter situation.

03:57.782 --> 03:59.875
As in I don't have enough
to both wash our clothes

03:59.900 --> 04:01.708
and park the RV on the street.

04:01.733 --> 04:03.287
The meters take credit cards, you know.

04:03.312 --> 04:05.460
Yeah, I don't really subscribe
to that whole thing...

04:05.485 --> 04:06.851
Being a prisoner to plastic.

04:06.876 --> 04:08.542
Life's got its own hidden fees, you know.

04:09.351 --> 04:11.504
Laundry room's through the kitchen.

04:11.529 --> 04:13.668
Great. [Whistles]

04:15.190 --> 04:16.587
Whoa!

04:16.676 --> 04:19.642
Lord, what did you do to his hair?

04:19.668 --> 04:21.470
- I washed it.
- With what?

04:21.495 --> 04:23.972
Shampoo. I don't know.
That soft soap we had.

04:24.206 --> 04:25.839
You brushed it, didn't you?

04:26.587 --> 04:27.964
What do you want to hear?

04:28.904 --> 04:31.991
Scotty, go upstairs and ask
Lucy for a scrunchie, okay?

04:32.016 --> 04:33.312
We'll get this under control.

04:33.337 --> 04:34.536
Okay.

04:36.011 --> 04:37.544
[Sighs]

04:39.153 --> 04:42.615
Uh, so I'm gathering black
hair care is like a thing?

04:42.640 --> 04:44.054
It's a science.

04:45.160 --> 04:47.800
Is this a... A ghost costume, Marc?

04:47.825 --> 04:49.425
No, those are our sheets.

04:49.450 --> 04:51.116
I've had those since
college. They were lucky.

04:51.141 --> 04:53.674
You have Scotty sleeping
on these raggedy-ass sheets?

04:53.699 --> 04:55.766
- Eh, he likes them.
- He likes syphilis?

04:55.791 --> 04:57.504
Okay, yeah, no.

04:57.529 --> 04:59.763
Uh, look, I appreciate
your concern and all,

04:59.788 --> 05:02.802
but Egyptian cottons aren't
exactly in the budget right now.

05:02.827 --> 05:05.323
Fine. I have some sheets at the shop.

05:05.348 --> 05:06.814
You can have them for free.

05:06.850 --> 05:08.397
Come and pick them up tomorrow.

05:08.422 --> 05:10.555
Did you tell Scotty he
could take my scrunchie?

05:10.580 --> 05:12.464
- Thanks for asking me, Mom.
- [Door slams]

05:12.489 --> 05:14.055
What do you say we go now?

05:14.293 --> 05:16.493
- Um...
- Now. Let's go now.

05:17.994 --> 05:21.028
[Organ music playing]

05:29.025 --> 05:32.306
Woman: Excuse me. Excuse me?

05:33.343 --> 05:36.143
Oh, there you are. Hi.

05:36.179 --> 05:38.473
Yes, I was wondering if this seat is taken.

05:38.498 --> 05:41.385
Oh, I'm sorry, I'm actually
saving it for a friend.

05:42.552 --> 05:46.254
[Cellphone dialing]

05:46.289 --> 05:48.543
<i>Hi. It's April,</i>
<i>leave me a message</i>

05:48.568 --> 05:49.687
<i>at the sound of the beep.</i>

05:49.712 --> 05:52.480
April, where are you? The
service is about to start.

05:52.505 --> 05:54.872
I'm center-left. Well, you can't miss me.

05:54.897 --> 05:56.697
I'm wearing an enormous hat.

05:56.722 --> 05:58.611
I'm now seriously rethinking...

05:58.636 --> 06:01.370
Shh! No cellphones in church.

06:03.000 --> 06:09.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

06:10.290 --> 06:11.622
[Bell rings]

06:13.360 --> 06:14.590
- Hi.
- Well, hi, there.

06:14.615 --> 06:15.847
How can I help you?

06:15.872 --> 06:17.838
Yeah, I need to find my sister.

06:22.538 --> 06:25.035
I need to know if you've booked
a trip for my sister recently.

06:25.070 --> 06:26.770
Her name is Savannah Davis.

06:26.805 --> 06:29.527
- And who are you?
- Her sister.

06:29.552 --> 06:31.992
Well, Savi's come here for years,

06:32.017 --> 06:33.450
but I've never seen you before.

06:33.475 --> 06:35.899
Well, that's because since
the advent of the Internet,

06:35.924 --> 06:37.734
most people use services like Expedia.

06:37.759 --> 06:40.402
But hold on... That, while convenient,

06:40.461 --> 06:43.963
may deprive them of the
beautiful human interaction

06:43.988 --> 06:46.656
that you and I are
having right now, Phyllis.

06:46.698 --> 06:48.598
Please, just help me.

06:48.634 --> 06:50.995
My boss won't like it... Privacy rights.

06:55.073 --> 06:56.239
Thank you.

06:56.275 --> 06:57.716
I'm not the only one that works here,

06:57.741 --> 07:00.339
- so I have to check the system.
- Check the system.

07:02.438 --> 07:03.863
- Aha!
- Aha?

07:03.899 --> 07:06.299
- Savi did book a trip with us.
- Where, Phyllis? Where?

07:06.334 --> 07:08.483
Australia, two years ago.

07:09.137 --> 07:11.068
A getaway for her and Harry.

07:16.311 --> 07:18.878
So, with the reviews the way they are,

07:18.914 --> 07:21.504
I plan on being way overbooked.

07:21.529 --> 07:24.197
Whoa, there he is, chef Harry Davis...

07:24.232 --> 07:26.599
The man, the myth, the legend.

07:26.634 --> 07:27.833
[Imitates crowd cheering]

07:28.339 --> 07:29.705
Pleasure to meet you, sir.

07:29.730 --> 07:30.996
Ellis Boone.

07:31.032 --> 07:32.798
Sorry, mate. Do I...

07:32.833 --> 07:34.633
I'm Greta's silent partner.

07:34.669 --> 07:37.064
Yeah, but now that the little
lady is opening a club in Paris,

07:37.089 --> 07:38.959
it would appear my silent days are over.

07:39.273 --> 07:40.377
I'll be taking care of

07:40.402 --> 07:42.438
all the pesky little
front-of-house details.

07:42.840 --> 07:44.606
Great. Uh, so this is a...

07:44.642 --> 07:46.113
Is this a staff meeting?

07:46.138 --> 07:49.011
- Should I have known about this?
- Uh, well, I don't know.

07:49.036 --> 07:52.437
Uh, do you see any kitchen guys here?

07:52.462 --> 07:55.329
Uh, no. You don't.

07:55.722 --> 07:58.523
So, I don't know. I
guess you're good to go.

07:58.548 --> 08:01.282
You can, uh, start your
prep. Mince your herbs.

08:01.307 --> 08:02.489
Okay.

08:02.748 --> 08:05.482
I'll, uh, ship off to work, then, shall I?

08:05.507 --> 08:07.341
- Okay, great.
- Okay. Uhp.

08:07.620 --> 08:10.366
- Boom. That's good stuff.
- Yeah.

08:10.391 --> 08:11.842
I'll be here if you need me, all right?

08:11.867 --> 08:13.049
- Excellent.
- All right.

08:13.074 --> 08:16.510
So, guys, this is what I was
thinking as far as sections...

08:16.984 --> 08:19.518
April: Do you like solids or patterns?

08:19.543 --> 08:21.347
Now, this one is soft.

08:22.133 --> 08:23.342
Marc?

08:25.762 --> 08:27.629
- Marc!
- Yo!

08:27.654 --> 08:30.154
"Yo"? I'm picking out your sheets?

08:30.325 --> 08:32.058
Thanks, April. You're awesome.

08:32.289 --> 08:34.222
So, that's an online university?

08:34.258 --> 08:36.725
No, I meant <i> you</i> should
be picking out your sheets.

08:36.760 --> 08:38.460
I dig the ones you're holding.

08:38.495 --> 08:40.662
And you're sure I can't
help you pay for them?

08:40.698 --> 08:42.164
Not without money.

08:42.869 --> 08:44.736
Why you got to do that
in front of the lady?

08:44.761 --> 08:46.261
- You're kind of killing my game.
- Kimmie, can you

08:46.296 --> 08:48.199
go and dust the shelves, please?

08:48.224 --> 08:49.497
Sure.

08:49.522 --> 08:51.321
[Chuckles lightly]

08:52.369 --> 08:54.068
You know I'm doing you a favor, right?

08:54.104 --> 08:55.570
She's not a good girl?

08:55.605 --> 08:57.633
With the sheets! The favor's the sheets!

08:57.658 --> 09:00.096
I normally sell these for 300 bucks.

09:00.121 --> 09:01.885
Well, that's a racket.

09:01.910 --> 09:04.010
Hey, are those cinnamon buns free?

09:04.281 --> 09:05.347
[Sighs]

09:05.882 --> 09:08.616
[Bell ringing]

09:22.299 --> 09:24.080
What the...

09:26.570 --> 09:28.493
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.

09:28.518 --> 09:30.346
What is... 8:30 to 9:00...

09:30.680 --> 09:32.062
What does this mean?

09:32.087 --> 09:33.706
What does this mean? Was I towed?

09:34.094 --> 09:35.460
Oh, you. I'm...

09:36.020 --> 09:37.319
Hey!

09:37.574 --> 09:40.391
- Hey. Hi.
- Oh, for the love of God.

09:40.416 --> 09:42.105
Did you... did you see what happened, huh?

09:42.130 --> 09:44.297
You just w... you just
watched them tow my car?

09:44.332 --> 09:46.127
First you take my space,
and then you just...

09:46.152 --> 09:47.749
You just watch them tow my car?!

09:47.774 --> 09:49.207
What kind of a person are you?

09:49.232 --> 09:51.146
I mean, w... What kind of a person am I?

09:51.171 --> 09:52.637
Just... Right? I deserve this.

09:52.662 --> 09:54.461
That's what's happening. I deserve this.

09:54.486 --> 09:55.652
- Get in the car.
- What?

09:55.677 --> 09:57.176
Get in the car. Look, I got...

09:57.201 --> 09:58.755
I have a picture of the
truck that towed your car.

09:58.780 --> 10:00.279
So, if you get in the car...

10:00.315 --> 10:01.614
- Yeah, can I...
- Hey, listen.

10:01.650 --> 10:03.397
Your freak-out's ruining my stakeout,

10:03.422 --> 10:05.033
- so just get in the car...
- Stakeout?

10:05.058 --> 10:06.496
[Laughing] What, are you a cop?

10:06.521 --> 10:07.787
Do I look like a cop?

10:07.822 --> 10:08.921
- No.
- Get in the car.

10:08.957 --> 10:10.523
- I'm not...
- Get in the car.

10:10.558 --> 10:12.247
- Get in the car!
- All right, I'm getting in!

10:12.272 --> 10:13.500
Crazy woman.

10:16.531 --> 10:18.531
[Sighs]

10:19.493 --> 10:22.459
Tissues. Beignets on the dash.

10:23.144 --> 10:25.808
What are these... are these
beignets from bottega Louie?

10:25.833 --> 10:29.535
Geez. Okay. This is a
seriously catered stakeout.

10:29.570 --> 10:32.322
- Who are you watching?
- My husband. My husband.

10:32.347 --> 10:35.218
My lying, cheating, eurotrash-screwing...

10:35.243 --> 10:37.910
- Okay.
- Pig bastard of a husband.

10:37.945 --> 10:39.345
His mistress lives there.

10:40.141 --> 10:41.687
I think.

10:42.116 --> 10:43.573
Look...

10:44.727 --> 10:48.035
Did you happen to see him when
you were walking past the lobby?

10:50.059 --> 10:52.234
Oh. You mean that guy?

10:55.830 --> 10:57.329
[Gasps] That's him.

10:57.365 --> 11:00.444
He's alone. He's alone. He's alone.

11:00.469 --> 11:03.124
Where's your slut?
Where's your slut, daddy?

11:03.149 --> 11:05.282
Come on, little slut, where are you?

11:05.317 --> 11:07.051
Oh, yeah, the slut's probably showering...

11:07.086 --> 11:09.045
- Post-sex rinse.
- Where is she?

11:11.414 --> 11:13.258
Sorry, yeah. Sorry.

11:17.266 --> 11:19.854
Do you want me to take you
to the tow yard or what?

11:20.175 --> 11:21.608
'Kay.

11:21.633 --> 11:23.700
[Indistinct talking in distance]

11:29.800 --> 11:31.400
Oh, who hung this here?

11:31.583 --> 11:33.448
Uh, I did, chef.

11:33.473 --> 11:35.139
Thought it might inspire you.

11:35.253 --> 11:36.586
Thanks, mate.

11:36.621 --> 11:38.221
[Crying]

11:38.256 --> 11:40.190
You okay?

11:40.225 --> 11:42.358
I just wanted to say what an honor...

11:42.427 --> 11:43.793
It was working with you, chef.

11:43.829 --> 11:45.845
[Chuckles] Laurie, what...

11:45.870 --> 11:48.498
- What's going on?
- Ellis just fired me.

11:49.633 --> 11:52.268
Me, Ava, Rico, Marco, all of us... gone.

11:52.304 --> 11:53.970
Okay, just... [Clears throat]

11:54.005 --> 11:56.873
Do not go anywhere.

11:56.908 --> 12:00.677
[Indistinct conversations]

12:06.222 --> 12:08.119
- What the...
- I need to see you outside.

12:08.144 --> 12:09.243
This is not the time.

12:09.279 --> 12:11.079
Yeah, it's the time. Let's go.

12:11.114 --> 12:13.173
Can you not see that I'm in a meeting here?

12:13.262 --> 12:15.922
[Clears throat] S... hey. I'm Harry.

12:16.126 --> 12:17.892
- Niko.
- Nice to meet you, Niko.

12:17.928 --> 12:19.394
Listen, I hate to interrupt your interview,

12:19.429 --> 12:20.695
but would you mind
stepping out so Ellis and I

12:20.731 --> 12:22.132
can talk about the menu real quick?

12:22.157 --> 12:23.824
- No problem.
- Thank you.

12:26.470 --> 12:28.412
I don't know who the
hell you think you are...

12:28.437 --> 12:29.925
You don't want to start with me like that.

12:29.950 --> 12:31.716
But you can't just strut in
here and fire all my staff

12:31.741 --> 12:33.560
because they're... let me guess,
what, they're not hot enough?

12:33.753 --> 12:35.486
- [Laughs]
- W... h-hey, it's not funny.

12:35.511 --> 12:37.177
Those people helped launch this place.

12:37.212 --> 12:39.462
The launch, my friend, is over.

12:39.487 --> 12:41.287
It's an event that has come and gone.

12:41.312 --> 12:43.234
I'm in charge of the nitty-gritty,

12:43.259 --> 12:44.888
and I want more pretty-pretty.

12:44.913 --> 12:47.110
Who are you? Really, you
talk like this in life?

12:47.135 --> 12:48.267
In fact,

12:48.292 --> 12:50.325
the only chick worth keeping

12:50.350 --> 12:53.251
was that party planner who quit.

12:53.276 --> 12:54.808
Just a sec, love.

12:54.833 --> 12:56.366
Now, what was her name again?

12:56.391 --> 12:58.557
It's, uh, Joss.

12:59.817 --> 13:03.951
Ooh, now, that was a ripe piece of ass.

13:03.976 --> 13:05.492
Hmm?

13:05.914 --> 13:07.873
Greta, darling.

13:08.150 --> 13:10.117
No, no, no, no. It's a fine time.

13:10.142 --> 13:12.442
No, my meeting was just
on his way out the door.

13:19.988 --> 13:22.255
- You're Karen Kim, yes?
- Yes.

13:22.290 --> 13:24.757
And this is in preparation
for the stem-cell retrieval

13:24.792 --> 13:26.435
- for Vivian Adams?
- That's correct.

13:26.460 --> 13:28.963
The drug in the injection
you're about to receive

13:28.988 --> 13:30.888
will stimulate the release of stem cells

13:30.924 --> 13:33.558
into your bloodstream to make
the retrieval process easier.

13:33.583 --> 13:35.717
You'll have one of these shots
a day for the next five days.

13:35.742 --> 13:37.071
Yes, I know. Thank you.

13:37.096 --> 13:38.963
Have your address and insurance changed?

13:38.998 --> 13:39.992
No.

13:40.017 --> 13:41.417
Your emergency contact is down here

13:41.442 --> 13:43.533
as Savannah Davis... Is that correct?

13:48.107 --> 13:50.858
Hey, thanks for sitting
for Scotty this morning.

13:50.883 --> 13:53.583
It really gave me a chance to
help Marc out with some things.

13:53.619 --> 13:56.186
Now, there is a guy who can
use all the help he can get.

13:56.221 --> 13:58.288
I think Uncle Marc's cool.

13:58.323 --> 13:59.790
"Uncle Marc"?

14:00.481 --> 14:02.614
Yeah, he's not technically your...

14:03.362 --> 14:04.961
Fine.

14:04.997 --> 14:06.763
I don't see why you
have a problem with him.

14:06.799 --> 14:10.682
No, I don't. I like him.
He's cool Uncle Marc.

14:13.603 --> 14:17.871
Anyway, since you did, in fact, babysit,

14:17.903 --> 14:22.373
I feel it's only right
if I... if I pay you.

14:22.408 --> 14:25.342
Pay me? He's my brother.

14:25.378 --> 14:26.944
What's wrong with you?

14:26.979 --> 14:28.133
Luc...

14:28.951 --> 14:30.884
[Sighs]

14:31.217 --> 14:32.816
So, how long you been married?

14:32.852 --> 14:36.012
[Sighs] Almost 10 years.

14:36.037 --> 14:38.833
Mm. [Scoffs] When did he start cheating?

14:38.858 --> 14:40.491
Doesn't matter.

14:40.526 --> 14:42.775
Oh, no. S-sorry.

14:42.800 --> 14:45.014
[Cellphone beeps] Oh, make a right here.

14:47.466 --> 14:49.033
You know, can I...

14:50.029 --> 14:52.521
- No, forget it.
- Go.

14:52.546 --> 14:54.038
Why do you stay?

14:54.206 --> 14:55.614
Money.

14:55.878 --> 14:58.708
Ah. Eh, not his money...

14:58.733 --> 15:01.611
My money. My money.

15:01.636 --> 15:03.371
- Oh. Well, then...
- If I don't have proof

15:03.371 --> 15:05.005
of his horny little habits,

15:05.030 --> 15:07.717
then I'm gonna have to pay
him half of my net worth.

15:07.742 --> 15:11.110
And that is not happening.
It is not happening.

15:11.145 --> 15:14.813
Not after the 20 years I've
spent building my brand.

15:14.849 --> 15:17.093
- Your brand?
- Yeah.

15:19.064 --> 15:21.242
Stop the train. You are not...

15:21.879 --> 15:24.822
[Gasps] Yes, you are!

15:24.847 --> 15:26.213
Calista Raines?!

15:26.249 --> 15:27.713
If you tweet this, I'll kill you.

15:27.738 --> 15:29.904
Oh, my God! I knew I recognized you!

15:29.929 --> 15:32.516
I... Calista frickin' Raines.

15:32.541 --> 15:33.974
Do you know that you are, like,

15:33.999 --> 15:35.965
one of my favorite designers of all time?

15:35.990 --> 15:37.990
I think I have four knock-offs of yours.

15:38.015 --> 15:39.877
Uh, I'm sorry.

15:39.902 --> 15:41.335
You're just... You're really expensive.

15:41.371 --> 15:43.961
What is a fashion force
like you doing driving around

15:43.986 --> 15:45.552
following your own husband?

15:45.577 --> 15:46.743
You're fabulous.

15:46.768 --> 15:48.286
W... you just hire a P.I. or something.

15:48.311 --> 15:50.244
Yeah, well, Luca sniffs them out

15:50.280 --> 15:52.726
and pays them twice as
much to back off, so...

15:52.751 --> 15:55.285
Well, you could at least cut
down on your stakeout time

15:55.310 --> 15:57.209
by doing that "find my iPhone" thing.

15:57.234 --> 15:59.234
- More.
- Are you serious right now?

15:59.259 --> 16:00.792
It's basically a tracking device.

16:00.817 --> 16:02.484
You just install it on his cellphone

16:02.509 --> 16:05.048
and you have cheater GPS...
It tells you where he is.

16:05.073 --> 16:07.466
You're a little frickin' genius!

16:07.491 --> 16:09.341
- Well, I'm a little crazy.
- You? Please.

16:09.366 --> 16:10.632
I've had nine coffees

16:10.667 --> 16:12.667
and three meals in the car today.

16:12.702 --> 16:14.302
Please, I know how this must look.

16:14.337 --> 16:16.304
No, no, believe me, I get it.

16:16.339 --> 16:18.493
Spending your life on the trail of somebody

16:18.518 --> 16:21.159
who doesn't want to be
found... Mm, I get it.

16:21.177 --> 16:22.494
Mm.

16:23.580 --> 16:26.681
I fell in love with
my sister's ex-husband,

16:26.716 --> 16:29.217
and, uh, two weeks ago, she
saw us kissing on the beach,

16:29.252 --> 16:31.085
disowned me, and split.

16:31.121 --> 16:33.293
So, I've been trying to
track her down ever since.

16:33.318 --> 16:36.127
Mm. I've always wanted a sister.

16:36.581 --> 16:38.454
Must be hard to lose one.

16:40.463 --> 16:44.065
Well, thank you for
saying that and only that.

16:45.835 --> 16:49.404
Okay. Looks like we're here.

16:49.439 --> 16:52.149
Oh. [Chuckles]

16:53.443 --> 16:56.544
Hey, listen, I hope that this

16:56.569 --> 16:58.703
isn't too f-forward or
anything, but it's...

16:58.738 --> 17:00.972
It's not every day that
I get ubered around by

17:01.007 --> 17:02.907
a world-famous designer whose clothes

17:02.942 --> 17:04.409
I would literally kill for.

17:04.444 --> 17:06.109
I just... I'm an event planner.

17:06.146 --> 17:07.944
That's my card. I don't know if...

17:07.981 --> 17:10.181
Well, I-I have a guy,
but I'll... I'll keep it.

17:10.215 --> 17:11.867
Cool.

17:12.352 --> 17:14.452
Buh-bye.

17:17.089 --> 17:19.357
Who's making this crap?!

17:19.392 --> 17:23.127
I-is this 'cause the fish
market was out of oysters?

17:23.163 --> 17:26.001
- No, Phil, it is not.
- [Clears throat]

17:27.329 --> 17:30.531
So, you really want to do
this in front of your people?

17:30.661 --> 17:32.507
What are we doing, Ellis?

17:33.606 --> 17:37.041
Um, uh, you know what,
guys? Let's just clear out.

17:37.077 --> 17:39.143
Okay, h-h-hop to it. Let's go.

17:41.195 --> 17:44.328
It's not your restaurant, Harry. It's mine.

17:44.353 --> 17:46.887
And it's Greta's... The
woman who hired me, yeah?

17:46.923 --> 17:48.282
Yeah, not so much.

17:48.307 --> 17:50.723
You see, ever since you stole
Scott Trosman's fiancée,

17:50.748 --> 17:53.840
he no longer wanted anything
to do with this place.

17:53.865 --> 17:55.709
So, he sold me his shares.

17:55.734 --> 17:59.102
I now own 65% of this restaurant.

17:59.127 --> 18:01.467
Yeah, I know.

18:01.506 --> 18:03.051
Thick with irony, isn't it?

18:03.076 --> 18:04.675
Anyway, back to our roles.

18:05.043 --> 18:07.056
I'm the owner. I'm out there.

18:07.081 --> 18:09.214
Like Paco the dishwasher,

18:09.239 --> 18:11.021
you work back here.

18:11.516 --> 18:14.417
You are not the face of this establishment.

18:14.452 --> 18:16.052
People do not come here to see you.

18:16.087 --> 18:18.087
They come with their
smartphones at the ready

18:18.122 --> 18:19.655
hoping beyond pathetic hope

18:19.690 --> 18:21.584
to catch a glimpse of
Greta Jager and that's it.

18:22.323 --> 18:25.447
So, from now on, know your role.

18:25.472 --> 18:27.525
Do not come barging into my office.

18:27.550 --> 18:30.867
Do not come out onto my
floor. Just cook or just quit.

18:30.892 --> 18:32.825
It's up to you.

18:37.341 --> 18:39.475
[Door closes] Joss, you home?

18:39.510 --> 18:41.043
Joss: I'm in the John.

18:57.887 --> 19:02.262
Oh, my God, you are not
gonna believe who I met today.

19:04.915 --> 19:06.688
What is it? What's that?

19:08.229 --> 19:10.389
A postcard from Savi.

19:13.484 --> 19:15.361
What does it say?

19:15.617 --> 19:18.324
Alive, well, in Italy.

19:19.697 --> 19:20.963
That's it?

19:21.698 --> 19:23.465
Yeah, that's it.

19:24.277 --> 19:25.924
Let me see it.

19:26.804 --> 19:28.504
- No.
- Give it to me.

19:28.539 --> 19:30.896
- Joss.
- Karen, let me see it.

19:32.309 --> 19:34.443
"Alive, fine, in Italy.

19:38.071 --> 19:39.671
Don't tell Joss."

19:47.087 --> 19:49.087
You want to talk about it?

19:49.112 --> 19:51.212
No. [Door closes]

19:56.625 --> 19:58.000
[Knocking on door]

19:58.448 --> 20:00.880
Okay, hold on. I'm coming.

20:02.498 --> 20:04.288
Scotty bit a kid.

20:04.313 --> 20:05.417
What?

20:05.442 --> 20:06.875
I got a call from the
school, I have an appointment

20:06.900 --> 20:08.849
with the principal later,
and he sounded pissed.

20:08.874 --> 20:10.420
I mean, apparently this
is a really big deal.

20:10.445 --> 20:11.808
- He can get suspended.
- What school?

20:11.833 --> 20:13.300
Uh, Cross Bridge Elementary.

20:13.384 --> 20:15.443
That is one of L.A.'s worst schools!

20:15.468 --> 20:17.000
Well, it's in the trailer-park district.

20:17.025 --> 20:18.331
Well, you couldn't have
found a better park?

20:18.356 --> 20:20.055
Well, there aren't as many RV communities

20:20.091 --> 20:21.523
in Beverly hills as one would think.

20:21.559 --> 20:23.325
Well, did you even
research the school at all?

20:23.361 --> 20:25.427
- I yelped it!
- You...

20:25.463 --> 20:27.429
Hey, I'm doing the best I can.

20:27.465 --> 20:29.006
Are you really, Marc?

20:29.031 --> 20:31.765
I mean, 'cause to me, it seems
like you are doing the bare minimum.

20:31.801 --> 20:33.747
You are hitting on sales girls.

20:33.772 --> 20:35.668
Scotty's sleeping on holey sheets.

20:35.738 --> 20:38.072
He's running around the
neighborhood with lunatic hair.

20:38.097 --> 20:39.377
He is probably getting picked on,

20:39.402 --> 20:41.163
which is probably why he bit.

20:41.188 --> 20:42.687
This isn't happening.

20:42.712 --> 20:45.073
But it is. It's happening and it's real.

20:45.167 --> 20:47.455
And you are gonna have to
start thinking about things

20:47.480 --> 20:49.247
in terms of what's best for Scotty.

20:49.272 --> 20:50.705
Whoa, whoa, whoa, how do you think

20:50.730 --> 20:52.196
I have been thinking about things?

20:52.221 --> 20:53.231
'Cause this situation

20:53.256 --> 20:54.856
is miles away from what's best for me.

20:54.881 --> 20:56.414
Well, welcome to parenting.

20:56.439 --> 20:58.307
Jump on in. Water's warm.

20:59.004 --> 21:01.137
You know the only reason we're here at all

21:01.162 --> 21:02.887
is because you reached out to my sister

21:02.912 --> 21:04.112
and you asked her for help.

21:05.968 --> 21:08.502
And really, that's all
I was asking from you.

21:08.936 --> 21:10.401
Okay, Marc...

21:10.426 --> 21:12.478
No, no, no. You know, I-I don't
think I need to take any more

21:12.503 --> 21:13.903
self-righteous crap from a woman

21:13.928 --> 21:15.993
who can't get her own
daughter to look at her.

21:16.018 --> 21:18.619
So, yeah, good luck with
your kid who hates you.

21:18.644 --> 21:20.069
Scotty and I will be on our way.

21:21.813 --> 21:24.918
[Door opens, closes]

21:26.753 --> 21:29.393
No, I need... I need to
speak with the hotel manager.

21:29.418 --> 21:32.118
Uh,<i> ci sei?</i>
<i>Direttore, bravissimo.</i>

21:32.143 --> 21:36.891
<i>Sto cercando</i> Savannah Davis.
Davis... "D"... <i> Pronto.</i>

21:38.125 --> 21:39.392
Amazing.

21:39.932 --> 21:41.478
Why don't you take a break?

21:41.503 --> 21:43.814
I can't go hiking with
you right now, Karen.

21:43.886 --> 21:45.504
You've been through the whole list.

21:46.017 --> 21:47.416
[Cellphone rings] Unknown number.

21:47.756 --> 21:49.102
Here we go... hello?

21:49.127 --> 21:51.299
Calista: Bastard's on
the move. Who is this?

21:51.324 --> 21:52.824
It's Calista.

21:52.849 --> 21:54.282
Oh, my God, hi.

21:54.307 --> 21:55.540
I did what you said.

21:55.565 --> 21:56.831
I hacked the system.

21:56.856 --> 21:58.849
- What?
- I hacked the system.

21:58.874 --> 22:00.988
I did th... uh, the
"find the phone" thingy.

22:01.013 --> 22:02.413
Did it work?

22:02.438 --> 22:04.638
Yes! I'm looking at his car now.

22:04.663 --> 22:06.796
It's going north on Flower.

22:06.821 --> 22:08.087
I'm telling you, he's going to that

22:08.112 --> 22:09.378
little cheesy hotel that he likes.

22:09.403 --> 22:11.094
I'm picking you up. I need your help.

22:11.119 --> 22:13.333
- Just tell me where you live.
- Okay, okay. Just...

22:13.358 --> 22:14.883
You need to take a breath before you drive.

22:14.908 --> 22:16.749
I'm texting you the address right now.

22:17.744 --> 22:19.043
[Door opens, closes]

22:28.103 --> 22:30.514
[Buttons clicking]

22:32.474 --> 22:34.741
Hey. It's Karen.

22:34.776 --> 22:36.910
Want some company?

22:39.181 --> 22:41.515
[Knock on door]

22:45.860 --> 22:47.041
Have a minute?

22:47.701 --> 22:49.247
Come on in.

23:00.491 --> 23:03.125
[Clears throat] Can I get you somethin'?

23:03.150 --> 23:04.850
No, thank you.

23:05.163 --> 23:09.165
I... I just wanted to come
by and say that I'm sorry.

23:09.683 --> 23:12.618
Things have been rough between
me and Lucy, as you know,

23:12.653 --> 23:14.810
and I'm not handling it very well.

23:15.474 --> 23:18.361
I am tense and I'm judgey...

23:18.386 --> 23:21.020
Are these the sheets I got you?!

23:21.162 --> 23:22.861
Sorry.

23:22.886 --> 23:24.201
I'm sorry.

23:24.383 --> 23:25.720
No, it's okay.

23:26.233 --> 23:27.585
You're right.

23:28.369 --> 23:30.452
I wasn't prepared for all this, April.

23:30.477 --> 23:33.611
I mean, I used to have Scotty
for like three hours at a time.

23:33.741 --> 23:36.175
You know, we'd hit up the
zoo or... or catch a movie,

23:36.210 --> 23:37.707
and then I'd drop him off.

23:39.083 --> 23:40.846
I mean, I love the kid, but...

23:40.881 --> 23:44.096
- I know you do.
- This is not how I live my life.

23:45.152 --> 23:47.352
I'm the guy who has nothing, owes nothing.

23:47.388 --> 23:49.221
That's not the log-line for a dad.

23:49.767 --> 23:51.534
So, what do you want to do?

23:51.559 --> 23:54.026
I don't know. I didn't ask for this.

23:54.061 --> 23:56.361
- Well, you took it.
- Well, maybe I shouldn't have.

23:56.397 --> 23:57.830
Maybe I should just call
Miranda and tell her,

23:57.865 --> 23:59.141
"look, you know, I'm sorry.
You got to come home."

23:59.166 --> 24:02.286
What do you say I help you?

24:02.740 --> 24:06.038
Not criticize and control you,

24:06.073 --> 24:08.207
but actually try and help you.

24:11.660 --> 24:13.929
I'm not psyched about
meeting that principal.

24:14.672 --> 24:16.164
I'll go with you.

24:16.189 --> 24:17.549
Thank you, God.

24:17.628 --> 24:19.923
I happen to be very good with principals.

24:20.132 --> 24:21.613
I don't doubt it.

24:23.981 --> 24:25.948
[Indistinct talking]

24:26.369 --> 24:28.467
Harry, please, just
call me or the restaurant

24:28.492 --> 24:31.151
- as soon as you get this.
- All right, everyone, listen up.

24:31.285 --> 24:32.985
Big night tonight.

24:33.010 --> 24:35.077
My friend Joe Zee is
coming in with an entourage

24:35.102 --> 24:36.635
of Hollywood players and the like,

24:36.660 --> 24:38.223
so I want perfection.

24:38.248 --> 24:39.689
Where is Harry?

24:39.714 --> 24:41.287
Uh, um, he hasn't... He hasn't shown.

24:41.312 --> 24:42.478
Are you kidding me?

24:42.503 --> 24:44.670
- U-uh, no, sir, I am not.
- Well, call him!

24:44.695 --> 24:45.727
I-I-I just did.

24:45.752 --> 24:47.142
- Call him again.
- Okay.

24:47.167 --> 24:49.000
- Okay.
- Okay.

24:51.075 --> 24:55.678
[Telephone ringing, rock music playing]

24:55.713 --> 24:57.553
♪ You're gonna come from that side ♪

24:57.578 --> 25:00.145
♪ sooner or later ♪

25:00.170 --> 25:02.454
♪ came from the outside ♪

25:03.654 --> 25:05.554
[Ringing continues]

25:05.590 --> 25:07.753
♪ You can't hold back time ♪

25:08.559 --> 25:11.927
[Ringing and music stop]

25:50.720 --> 25:52.186
Hey!

25:52.221 --> 25:54.121
Come on in. Don't be shy.

25:56.187 --> 25:57.686
Ooh, what's this?

25:57.711 --> 25:59.154
Soothing aromatherapy

25:59.179 --> 26:00.708
and a manicure kit.

26:00.755 --> 26:03.354
Ugh! How did you know? My nails are a mess.

26:03.393 --> 26:05.760
When things get real,
it's the first thing to go.

26:06.042 --> 26:08.042
[Sighs] Sit.

26:08.067 --> 26:10.142
Mm. How are you?

26:10.167 --> 26:12.234
Oh, I feel like something from the future.

26:12.508 --> 26:13.641
Although in the future

26:13.676 --> 26:15.142
everything will probably be wireless.

26:15.177 --> 26:16.477
Probably.

26:16.512 --> 26:18.445
So, why are you here?

26:18.481 --> 26:20.069
Whoa! You get right to it.

26:20.094 --> 26:21.961
Life's too short. Screw the pretenses.

26:22.084 --> 26:24.785
I have been thinking about you a lot,

26:24.820 --> 26:27.187
and my day happened to get free.

26:29.658 --> 26:32.366
Today was supposed to be my monthly spa day

26:32.391 --> 26:33.997
with my best friend, Savi.

26:34.022 --> 26:35.322
What happened?

26:35.347 --> 26:37.881
- She fled the country.
- Oh.

26:37.906 --> 26:40.840
Without so much as a goodbye
or an explanation, either,

26:40.865 --> 26:43.632
leaving me to fear her
kidnapped or dead or worse.

26:43.657 --> 26:45.189
What's worse than dead?

26:45.214 --> 26:46.246
I don't know!

26:46.271 --> 26:47.370
I don't know...

26:47.395 --> 26:48.728
I'm pissed off.

26:48.753 --> 26:50.453
I'm not the one that hurt her.

26:50.478 --> 26:51.911
I didn't kiss her ex-husband.

26:52.084 --> 26:53.884
- Who did?
- Her sister.

26:53.909 --> 26:55.179
Oh.

26:55.204 --> 26:58.389
So, she's hurt and she's
mad and embarrassed.

26:58.414 --> 27:01.320
I get it. But she knew I was
going through some stuff, too,

27:01.345 --> 27:04.189
and not a word from her for two weeks.

27:04.214 --> 27:05.980
Two weeks of unanswered calls

27:06.005 --> 27:09.306
and e-mails and texts, not to
mention the sleepless nights.

27:10.569 --> 27:13.322
She was supposed to be my family.

27:13.832 --> 27:15.906
I didn't move to Boston with a guy

27:15.931 --> 27:17.944
because she was my family.

27:17.969 --> 27:19.636
Were you in love with him?

27:19.671 --> 27:22.838
- No.
- [Sighs] Karen.

27:22.863 --> 27:25.490
I'm sorry, I shouldn't be
burdening you with this.

27:25.515 --> 27:28.298
Okay, the last thing
that you are is a burden.

27:28.323 --> 27:30.351
- But...
- But?

27:30.376 --> 27:34.060
But it sounds like your
friend has had a hard blow

27:34.085 --> 27:36.352
and is taking some time for herself.

27:36.377 --> 27:38.043
What's so bad about that?

27:38.068 --> 27:40.735
Look, when I get angry like you are...

27:40.760 --> 27:41.868
You get angry?

27:41.893 --> 27:43.760
Hard to believe, I know.

27:43.795 --> 27:45.114
But when I do,

27:45.630 --> 27:47.773
I usually end up realizing that

27:47.798 --> 27:52.488
underneath all that anger,
I'm really just scared.

27:55.324 --> 27:57.858
So, what are you scared of, Karen?

28:05.439 --> 28:06.847
I'm here.

28:08.235 --> 28:09.437
Okay...

28:09.462 --> 28:10.843
I'm looking.

28:11.909 --> 28:14.821
I don't see him. Are you
sure this is the place?

28:14.846 --> 28:16.913
No, I-I'm not parking.
Not parking, not parking.

28:16.949 --> 28:18.548
Go away. Yes, it is the place.

28:18.584 --> 28:20.712
Look... his... His cell is tracking here.

28:20.737 --> 28:22.016
He's... he's there.

28:22.041 --> 28:24.197
- Just keep looking.
- Okay, I'm looking.

28:24.556 --> 28:26.989
Okay, I'm... Thank you for doing this.

28:27.014 --> 28:29.254
Oh, please, this is
the greatest distraction

28:29.279 --> 28:30.483
from my very sad life.

28:31.448 --> 28:33.481
Okay. Not him. Not him.

28:34.181 --> 28:36.748
Oh, very cute guy, but not him.

28:38.588 --> 28:40.789
[Gasps] Oh, God, it's him.

28:40.824 --> 28:43.359
It's him? Who's he with?

28:43.461 --> 28:45.393
Is he with the... the...

28:45.462 --> 28:47.329
The woman with the ostrich legs,

28:47.364 --> 28:48.563
the blond girl?

28:48.598 --> 28:51.032
- I think he's alone.
- Crap!

28:51.068 --> 28:52.500
Oh, no, no, no, wait.

28:52.536 --> 28:54.569
The waiter just brought him two champagnes.

28:54.604 --> 28:56.169
So, he's meeting someone.

28:56.194 --> 28:58.395
Or he's thirsty or celebratory.

28:58.430 --> 29:01.264
I'm sure he's gonna stick
his tongue down her throat

29:01.299 --> 29:04.300
as soon as she gets there,
'cause that's how classy he is.

29:04.336 --> 29:06.817
So, just get ready to snap a photo.

29:06.842 --> 29:08.475
Yeah, yeah, yeah! I got this covered.

29:15.195 --> 29:16.661
Ooh, wow.

29:16.686 --> 29:19.548
Those are ostrich legs,
aren't they? That is so weird.

29:19.573 --> 29:20.740
She's there?

29:20.765 --> 29:22.492
Yeah, I think so.

29:22.517 --> 29:23.849
Yeah. He's getting up.

29:23.946 --> 29:25.625
She's walking over.

29:25.650 --> 29:30.630
I got him, that scum-sucker.
I got him. I finally got him.

29:30.655 --> 29:31.987
[Cellphone beeps]

29:32.012 --> 29:33.678
Oh, uh, uh, I think it's a European number.

29:33.771 --> 29:36.167
It's... it's... I think it's Italy. Hello?

29:36.192 --> 29:38.293
No, no. J... Joss?

29:38.328 --> 29:40.634
Savi, I can't hear you.
Can you hear me? Hello?

29:40.659 --> 29:43.293
Wait, hello, Savi? Please don't
hang up. I can't hear you yet.

29:43.318 --> 29:44.618
Hello? Hello?

29:44.643 --> 29:46.376
Hello? Shoot. Hello? Yes, hello.

29:46.401 --> 29:49.770
This is the manager of Luna Hotel Baglioni.

29:50.967 --> 29:53.418
The woman you are looking for was here,

29:53.443 --> 29:55.510
but she left a week ago.

29:55.545 --> 29:57.378
I don't know where she go. I'm sorry.

29:57.414 --> 29:58.980
<i>Grazie.</i>

29:59.467 --> 30:01.197
Joss?! Joss!

30:01.222 --> 30:03.082
- Oh, hi. I'm...
- Joss, what's happening?

30:03.107 --> 30:04.607
I'm sorry. I'm sorry. I'm here.

30:04.632 --> 30:06.232
I'm having a heart attack over here.

30:06.257 --> 30:08.624
Joss, did you get the photo?

30:18.606 --> 30:20.472
I thought this was a restaurant.

30:20.508 --> 30:22.775
That's weird, 'cause there's no food.

30:22.810 --> 30:24.877
Um... excuse me.

30:24.912 --> 30:28.425
Uh, can you just check on
our order, please? Thank you.

30:28.785 --> 30:31.795
I am so sorry, everyone. Really, I am.

30:31.820 --> 30:33.902
The restaurant biz, you know?

30:33.927 --> 30:36.464
This is not rare, okay? Rare is bloody.

30:36.489 --> 30:38.586
Does this look bloody? How
are you gonna un-cook that?

30:38.611 --> 30:40.787
Sorry I'm late, folks. Let's do this.

30:40.812 --> 30:42.992
- What's going out, Phil?
- Uh, everything. I don't know.

30:43.017 --> 30:44.626
Okay, big breath. I've got this. I got it.

30:44.651 --> 30:46.106
Ellis was on a rampage earlier.

30:46.131 --> 30:48.065
He's out there with a table of six VIPs.

30:48.100 --> 30:49.399
If I were you, I'd steer clear.

30:49.435 --> 30:51.568
VIPs you say.

30:51.604 --> 30:53.058
Who are they?

30:55.028 --> 30:56.073
Ah.

30:56.108 --> 30:57.274
Sorry for the wait, folks.

30:57.309 --> 30:59.441
- Oh, good, good.
- Oh, finally.

30:59.466 --> 31:01.922
Thank God. I was going to fall over.

31:01.947 --> 31:05.682
I was personally making
some off-the-menu dishes.

31:05.718 --> 31:07.551
Okay, we have roast beet
salad with horseradish

31:07.586 --> 31:08.986
and salmon roe on brioche toast

31:09.021 --> 31:11.338
and seared scallop with carrot olive oil

31:11.363 --> 31:13.630
and citrus tapenade. Please, enjoy.

31:13.665 --> 31:15.203
All right, we got it. Thank you.

31:18.991 --> 31:20.724
Mmm.

31:20.749 --> 31:22.276
Oh, my God.

31:23.078 --> 31:26.122
I have to say, this dish is everything.

31:26.147 --> 31:29.481
I mean, it's... it's
innovative. It's whimsical.

31:29.506 --> 31:31.005
It's flavor times flavor.

31:31.030 --> 31:33.260
Thank you. Thank you.
You're just as descriptive

31:33.285 --> 31:35.285
in real life as you are
on "All on the Line."

31:35.320 --> 31:37.053
You don't watch my show.

31:37.089 --> 31:39.623
Oh, please. Are you kidding? It's major.

31:39.658 --> 31:41.791
[Laughter]

31:41.827 --> 31:43.560
Oh, I think I'm falling over again.

31:43.595 --> 31:46.263
I mean, you're smart, you're
talented, and you're handsome.

31:46.298 --> 31:49.379
Seriously, Ellis, you should
make it an open kitchen.

31:49.404 --> 31:51.738
It's a shame not to be
able to watch him all night.

31:51.773 --> 31:53.306
Oh, I-I couldn't possibly work

31:53.342 --> 31:55.742
all distracted by beautiful
ladies such as yourself.

31:55.777 --> 31:57.711
It's just... Aww. Please, enjoy.

32:01.717 --> 32:04.994
Well, can't you make room in
the class for one more kid?

32:05.019 --> 32:06.785
He's very small.

32:07.919 --> 32:09.719
O-okay. Thanks.

32:09.744 --> 32:11.874
Oh, my God! I am so sorry!

32:11.899 --> 32:14.099
I know I was supposed to
meet you at church yesterday.

32:14.124 --> 32:15.356
Things have been so crazy.

32:16.451 --> 32:18.284
Honey, what is it?

32:19.922 --> 32:21.621
Do I fall out?

32:23.358 --> 32:25.458
Of the group?

32:25.493 --> 32:26.982
What are you talking about?

32:27.187 --> 32:29.754
Without Savi, do I fall out?

32:31.220 --> 32:34.888
I'm afraid with her gone,
our friendship will fade.

32:34.973 --> 32:38.208
She was the glue, the
one who brought me in.

32:38.673 --> 32:40.840
And I know Joss is like your sister.

32:40.875 --> 32:43.643
Oh, my God, come here.
You are spinning out.

32:43.678 --> 32:45.745
I know.

32:45.780 --> 32:48.147
Freakin' postcard.

32:48.182 --> 32:50.149
Right?! What was that?!

32:50.184 --> 32:51.332
I can't even.

32:51.830 --> 32:56.366
Listen to me, Savi or no
Savi, you are my sister, too.

32:57.156 --> 32:58.989
I may miss things because of Lucy,

32:59.014 --> 33:01.515
but you are never falling out of anything.

33:01.550 --> 33:03.950
And our friendship better
not fade, because I need you.

33:03.986 --> 33:07.187
I need, like, six therapists right now.

33:07.222 --> 33:10.099
- What's going on?
- My daughter isn't talking to me

33:10.124 --> 33:12.896
and I seem to have adopted a third child

33:12.921 --> 33:15.588
in the form of a migrating 32-year-old man.

33:15.631 --> 33:17.798
[Laughs]

33:17.833 --> 33:19.065
[Sighs]

33:19.101 --> 33:20.333
I think I may have an idea

33:20.369 --> 33:21.818
on how to fix everything, though.

33:21.843 --> 33:23.376
Can I run it by you?

33:28.191 --> 33:29.857
I'm sorry.

33:29.882 --> 33:31.929
- It's fine.
- No, I'm really sorry.

33:32.161 --> 33:35.496
It's really fine. Can I
have another one of these?

33:35.521 --> 33:37.257
I really thought it was my sister.

33:37.282 --> 33:39.366
Right. Yes. Let's talk about that.

33:39.391 --> 33:40.924
Let's talk about that. So what's...

33:40.959 --> 33:42.520
What's his name, again? Harry?

33:42.545 --> 33:43.625
- Harry.
- Harry.

33:43.650 --> 33:45.116
Do you love him?

33:45.141 --> 33:48.065
- Oh, yeah.
- Well, did she?

33:48.530 --> 33:50.273
- Who?
- Your sister.

33:50.298 --> 33:51.997
Well, he was her husband.

33:52.022 --> 33:54.055
Yeah, she cheated on him, she dumped him,

33:54.080 --> 33:55.980
and she left him for dead, so to me,

33:56.005 --> 33:58.905
she sounds like she's not
worth the sturm and drang.

33:58.930 --> 34:00.399
Yeah, I don't know what that means.

34:00.424 --> 34:03.258
It means stop being so hard on yourself.

34:03.283 --> 34:06.350
So what? She caught you in
a "here to eternity" moment

34:06.375 --> 34:07.807
with her ex.

34:07.843 --> 34:10.409
While my fiancé was
waiting for me at the altar.

34:12.716 --> 34:14.538
- Okay.
- Yeah.

34:14.837 --> 34:16.831
Well, this Harry must be

34:16.856 --> 34:19.612
something pretty special, then, right?

34:19.675 --> 34:22.579
He is. He's the one.

34:22.603 --> 34:25.505
I just wish that I could work through

34:25.531 --> 34:28.304
all this horrible ugly
stuff so that I can get to

34:28.330 --> 34:30.433
the beautiful thing that I
know I have waiting for me.

34:30.458 --> 34:32.257
- Just do it.
- How?

34:33.225 --> 34:36.536
I have an idea. Okay, I'm her.

34:36.572 --> 34:38.170
I'm your sister. Tell me.

34:38.206 --> 34:39.572
- What are you talking about?
- Tell me.

34:39.608 --> 34:41.007
Tell me what you want to say.

34:41.043 --> 34:42.409
- I'm... I'm her. Savi.
- Let me get the e-mail.

34:42.444 --> 34:44.811
- Okay, hold on.
- No, no e-mail. No e-mail.

34:44.846 --> 34:46.179
Joss, just say it. Just say it. Say it.

34:46.214 --> 34:47.746
I don't know what I'm supposed to say.

34:47.783 --> 34:48.748
"Savi." "Savi." Okay.

34:48.784 --> 34:51.351
- Um, Savi.
- Mm-hmm?

34:51.386 --> 34:53.520
I need you not to hate me.

34:53.554 --> 34:54.853
Why?

34:54.889 --> 34:57.324
Because I can't live with that.

34:57.359 --> 34:59.159
- Of course you can. Next.
- No, I can't.

34:59.194 --> 35:00.860
I can't.

35:00.896 --> 35:03.563
You can, Joss. You can.

35:03.599 --> 35:06.700
It'll be uncomfortable, it'll suck,

35:06.735 --> 35:11.338
and you'll feel loss...
But you can live with it.

35:12.941 --> 35:15.175
Unless you want to live without Harry.

35:20.748 --> 35:23.848
Everyone's glass is
full? Here's to you, chef.

35:23.895 --> 35:27.590
Here's to Google. Without it, I
wouldn't have known that Joe Q from...

35:27.615 --> 35:29.150
- Joe Zee.
- It's Joe Zee?

35:29.175 --> 35:31.008
Zee. Joe Zee... from my ass.

35:31.033 --> 35:32.599
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

35:32.624 --> 35:35.692
[Clears throat] Can I, uh, see you?

35:36.665 --> 35:37.751
Please?

35:38.844 --> 35:40.923
Well, I'm in a meeting.

35:41.453 --> 35:45.435
Um, Joe just called, and
apparently the Sundance channel

35:45.460 --> 35:48.400
is throwing some kind of
big party on Friday and, uh,

35:49.694 --> 35:51.794
he wants you to come.

35:51.886 --> 35:54.352
Well, you tell Joe I
said thank you very much,

35:54.377 --> 35:58.144
but I'll be working in
my restaurant that night.

36:01.082 --> 36:03.314
Oh, and Ellis?

36:04.646 --> 36:07.951
I'll be hiring all my
people back, too, okay?

36:34.127 --> 36:36.461
[Cellphone vibrates]

36:44.226 --> 36:46.826
I can't believe you're
calling me in this moment.

36:47.324 --> 36:50.900
Hi. Y-you're there.

36:50.925 --> 36:52.558
I didn't think you'd actually pick up.

36:52.583 --> 36:55.317
Oh, well, then, why did you call me?

36:55.732 --> 36:58.011
To leave a soliloquy on your voice-mail.

36:58.468 --> 37:01.801
Well, then, I'll hang up
and you can call me back.

37:01.826 --> 37:03.125
No, don't. Don't.

37:03.507 --> 37:05.707
Don't go anywhere.

37:05.742 --> 37:08.090
I just wanted to say thank you.

37:08.678 --> 37:10.225
For what?

37:10.614 --> 37:13.081
Well, I was, uh... [Clears throat]

37:13.116 --> 37:15.583
I was ready to quit Wunderbar today.

37:15.619 --> 37:17.085
Why?

37:17.120 --> 37:19.154
Oh, it's really not worth getting into,

37:19.189 --> 37:21.456
but let's just say I
was halfway down the road

37:21.491 --> 37:23.324
to throwing it all away...

37:23.910 --> 37:27.529
When I remembered how you fought for me,

37:27.564 --> 37:30.231
how you fought for me not
to go back to Australia,

37:30.267 --> 37:32.901
and how you fought for me
to get this rock-star job,

37:32.936 --> 37:35.826
and to keep it when things
got weird with Greta.

37:35.851 --> 37:38.434
And when you weren't there
during this little rough patch,

37:38.459 --> 37:40.593
I actually had to do some
fighting for myself, Joss,

37:40.628 --> 37:42.428
and y... You know what?

37:42.463 --> 37:45.431
I... I did it in a way
you'd be proud of, I think.

37:45.466 --> 37:47.066
In a way that didn't wreck

37:47.101 --> 37:49.013
everything that we worked for together.

37:49.604 --> 37:54.073
Harry... I really miss you.

37:54.904 --> 37:56.409
I miss you.

37:56.444 --> 37:59.412
[Sighs]

38:00.272 --> 38:01.905
So, what's this about?

38:01.940 --> 38:03.684
You'll know in a sec.

38:04.152 --> 38:06.943
Well, I see you've relaxed on
the whole controlling thing.

38:07.856 --> 38:10.113
Don't make me regret what I'm about to say.

38:10.148 --> 38:11.323
All right, guys.

38:11.348 --> 38:14.366
Put that down for a sec. I
have something to propose.

38:14.391 --> 38:16.057
[Clears throat]

38:16.082 --> 38:19.383
How do you all feel about
Marc and Scotty living here

38:19.408 --> 38:21.141
with us for a while?

38:21.166 --> 38:22.899
Oh, my gosh!

38:22.924 --> 38:25.258
There's a... a bedroom
right off the kitchen,

38:25.283 --> 38:27.474
plus you can use this address to get Scotty

38:27.499 --> 38:28.824
into a good neighborhood school.

38:28.849 --> 38:31.427
- I don't want to be a burden.
- You won't be.

38:31.685 --> 38:32.784
What do you say, kids?

38:32.820 --> 38:36.088
Yes! Yes! This is awesome.

38:36.123 --> 38:38.590
She's smiling. She's actually smiling.

38:42.939 --> 38:45.006
Oh, my gosh, it's gonna be so much fun!

38:50.966 --> 38:52.620
Bring it in.

38:52.645 --> 38:54.776
♪ There is a light
to all this darkness ♪

38:54.801 --> 38:56.327
♪ I will tell you this ♪

38:56.352 --> 38:59.887
♪ there's redemption in you
asking them just why it is ♪

38:59.912 --> 39:02.913
♪ some answers are
better left unspoken ♪

39:02.938 --> 39:06.306
♪ when you know you ain't
getting any younger ♪

39:06.331 --> 39:07.964
♪ younger, younger, are you? ♪

39:07.989 --> 39:10.657
